HEADWORD: Dipterocarpus
<hw>Dip`te*ro*car"pus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <?/ with two wings + <?/ fruit.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
genus of trees found in the East Indies, some species of which produce a
fragrant resin, other species wood oil. The fruit has two long
wings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

